FBIS4-17074 "drsov077_d_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs Murmansk To Become Largest Gas Extraction Base Murmansk To Become Largest Gas Extraction Base PM2004091194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 First Edition p 1 PM2004091194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA/ITAR-TASS report under the "Yesterday, Today, and Tomorrow" rubric: "Murmansk Is Russian Gas El Dorado"] [Text] The world's largest city within the Arctic circle, Murmansk, is destined to also become the world's largest base for the extraction of natural gas. Not far from it on a shelf in the Barents Sea, gigantic deposits of this fuel have been discovered. But while preparatory work prior to the marine deposits' exploitation is in progress, the city will feed from the West Siberian gas pipelines.
